Linear Regression Practice¶

Problem Statement¶

A company want predict their sell based on the amount they are spending on the advertisement on 3 media TV, Radio and Newspaper. So create a model that can help company to increase their sells based on advertisement.

Build a Model¶


















In [9]:



     


### SCIKIT-LEARN ###
# Consider one varibale at a time to build a linear regression model.
# Randomised the data and then split the data into train and test

X = data.iloc[:,:2] # here we are not considering Newpaper as it is not having any relationship with target Sales.
Y = data['Sales']

X_train, X_test, Y_train, Y_test = train_test_split(X,Y, train_size=0.8, random_state= 50, shuffle=True)

print (X_train.head())



     






















    
    






        TV  Radio
171   50.0   11.6
184  287.6   43.0
39    43.1   26.7
154  171.3   39.7
41   202.5   22.3
























In [10]:



     


# instantiate and fit
lm2 = LinearRegression()
lm2.fit(X_train, Y_train)

# print the coefficients
print(lm2.intercept_)
print(lm2.coef_)



     






















    
    






2.6999542439293034
[0.04704245 0.1888484 ]
























In [11]:



     


#Predict the sales for tetst data set 
y_predict = lm2.predict(X_test)



     



















In [12]:



     


metrics.r2_score(Y_test,y_predict)



     






















    
    
Out[12]:








0.8516296176286774




























Here R-square value is 0.85 which represents that 85% of Sales variance can be explain by using TV and Radio.



















In [13]:



     


Ex_variance = metrics.explained_variance_score(Y_test,y_predict)
MAR=metrics.mean_absolute_error(Y_test,y_predict)
MSR=metrics.mean_squared_error(Y_test,y_predict)



     



















In [14]:



     


print ("Our Model is having Expalined variance {} \n Mean Absolute Error {} \n Mean Squared Error {}".format(Ex_variance,MAR,MSR))



     






















    
    






Our Model is having Expalined variance 0.8518798198567745 
 Mean Absolute Error 1.1148794924799597 
 Mean Squared Error 2.1124789579050955




























Conclusion¶






















Here we can conclude that sales is having linear positive relationship with TV and Radio advertisement. Most effective advertisement mode is TV and Radio is less than TV. News Paper advertisement is not contributing to sales so company can focus on TV and Radio advertisements only to increase their sell and should not waste money on News Paper advertisements. These sells values can be predicted by the model with 85% explain variance.
